Set Publish Directory:
client/dist

Add environment variables starting with VITE_.

Deploy your site.

Ensure netlify.toml is in the root of your repository with the correct publish directory and redirect rules for React Router.

ğŸ”„ CI/CD Setup (GitHub Actions)

The repository includes workflows:

Frontend CI/CD

frontend-ci.yml: Runs tests and builds React app.

frontend-cd.yml: Deploys build to Netlify automatically.

Backend CI/CD

backend-ci.yml: Runs tests and linter.

backend-cd.yml: Triggers Render deployment on push.

Add GitHub secrets:

NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN & NETLIFY_SITE_ID for frontend.

RENDER_DEPLOY_HOOK for backend.

